# Slidev PPT Template Guide

## Overview
Use [temp/slides2.md](mdc:temp/slides2.md) as the template for generating presentations. All new presentations should follow this structure but be created in [slides.md](mdc:slides.md) in the root directory.

## Template Features
The template includes:
- Theme settings (seriph)
- Background image configuration
- Title and metadata setup
- Slide transitions
- Various layouts (section, two-cols-header, TwoRowSplit)
- Image integration
- Proper formatting for text and headings

## Usage Guidelines
1. New presentations should maintain the same structure and layout types
2. Update the title, team information, and content as needed
3. Keep the same transition and theme settings
4. Place all new slide images in `/image/slides/` directory
5. All final presentations should be saved in the root `slides.md` file, not in the temp directory
